    { question: "Normal sinus rhythm has a rate of:", options: ["40-60 bpm", "60-100 bpm", "80-120 bpm", "100-150 bpm"], correct: 1, rationale: "Normal sinus rhythm is 60-100 bpm with regular R-R intervals, upright P waves in lead II preceding each QRS, PR interval 0.12-0.20 seconds, and QRS duration <0.12 seconds. Below 60 is sinus bradycardia; above 100 is sinus tachycardia." }
